  <body id="s">
    <ul>
      <li>Opposing pathways that are both thermodynamically favorable</li>
    </ul>
    <p> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -Operate in opposite direction</p>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -End product of one is the starting compound of the
      other</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Reversible reactions are used by both pathways</li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      <li>Irreversible reaction of glycolysis must be bypassed in
        gluconeogenesis</li>
    </ul>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -Highly thermodynamically favorable, and regulated<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -Different enzymes in the different pathways<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -Differentially regulated to prevent a futile cycle</p>
